div.p:
Convinced that the status of the possessions of non-American states in the
                    Americas is a matter for common concern on the part of the American
                    republics;

Whereas, the representatives of the American republics
have signed a convention relating to regions in this hemisphere belonging to or
claimed by non-American states;

Whereas, situations may develop prior to the coming
into force of the said convention necessitating action on the part of the
American republics to protect their peace and safety;
